author: Charles Mackay
content: There is scarcely an occurrence in nature which, happening at a certain time,
  is not looked upon by some persons as a prognosticator either of good or evil. The
  latter are in the greatest number, so much more ingenious are we in tormenting ourselves
  than in discovering reasons for enjoyment in the things that surround us.
